Project Overview

Application name:

WorkBalance

Purpose:

Track office working hours and calculate monthly work-time balance.

Each workday contains only:

* First Check In
* Last Check Out

Multiple work sessions are NOT supported.

Worked Time is calculated as:

Worked Time = Check Out − Check In − Lunch Break

Lunch Break:

* Default: 45 minutes
* Editable per day
* Configurable in Settings

Standard workday:

8 hours 45 minutes

⸻

Main Features

The application calculates:

* Today’s worked time
* Remaining work time today
* Recommended leave time today
* Daily balance
* Monthly accumulated balance
* Monthly average worked time
* Monthly total worked time

The most important feature is calculating today’s recommended leave time.

⸻

Widget

The application includes a Home Screen widget.

The widget provides:

* Check In
* Check Out

Pressing a button immediately stores the current time.

If today’s record does not exist:

Create it automatically.

Check In:

* Store only the first check-in.
* Ask before replacing an existing value.

Check Out:

* Always keep the latest check-out.

⸻

Storage

Use SwiftData.

Store data locally.

Do not introduce CloudKit unless explicitly requested.

The data layer must be compatible with App Groups so the application, widget and App Intents share the same data.

⸻

Business Logic

Create dedicated services for calculations.

Examples:

* WorkTimeCalculator
* StatisticsCalculator

Business logic must remain independent from UI.

Services should be reusable from:

* App
* Widget
* App Intents
* Tests

⸻

Testing

Use Apple’s modern Testing framework.

Prioritize testing:

* Calculators
* Repository
* Business rules

Avoid unnecessary UI tests.

